00:03:40.630 --> 00:03:43.930
MALE SPEAKER: What's the
mathematical or natural

00:03:43.930 --> 00:03:49.110
scientific advantage to having a
Fibonacci number of spirals?

00:03:49.110 --> 00:03:50.110
JAMES GRIME: Well, there
is an advantage.

00:03:50.110 --> 00:03:54.600
Because by having a Fibonacci
number of spirals it allows

00:03:54.600 --> 00:03:56.830
the seeds to be packed
efficiently.

00:03:56.830 --> 00:04:01.600
So if you packed them like it
was spokes on a bicycle--

00:04:01.600 --> 00:04:07.010
let's say it was every quarter
turn, so you get four spikes

00:04:07.010 --> 00:04:08.390
coming out from the center.

00:04:08.390 --> 00:04:10.290
You've got all this
dead space.

00:04:10.290 --> 00:04:12.100
That'd be no good.

00:04:12.100 --> 00:04:13.650
So you don't want to
pack it like that.

00:04:13.650 --> 00:04:17.130
Maybe you want a pack
it every 12th.

00:04:17.130 --> 00:04:20.009
You do a 12th turn, and then you
put one in, and then you

00:04:20.009 --> 00:04:21.240
do a 12th turn and put one in.

00:04:21.240 --> 00:04:23.300
But again, you get lots
of dead space.

00:04:23.300 --> 00:04:26.650
So you don't want it to be a
fraction of a full circle.

00:04:26.650 --> 00:04:28.380
So you want it to be an
irrational number.

00:04:28.380 --> 00:04:31.500
So by doing that, it packs
them in more tightly.

00:04:31.500 --> 00:04:34.650
If the irrational number can be
approximated, though, by a

00:04:34.650 --> 00:04:38.470
fraction, you'll still get quite
a lot of dead space.

00:04:38.470 --> 00:04:42.020
What you want is an irrational
number that can't be

00:04:42.020 --> 00:04:43.670
approximated with a fraction--

00:04:43.670 --> 00:04:47.030
or at least approximated
really badly.

00:04:47.030 --> 00:04:50.710
Now, there is an irrational
number that is the most

00:04:50.710 --> 00:04:51.810
irrational number.

00:04:51.810 --> 00:04:55.130
By which I mean it can't
be approximated by

00:04:55.130 --> 00:04:56.980
fractions very well.

00:04:56.980 --> 00:04:59.350
That is a number called
the golden ratio.

00:04:59.350 --> 00:05:01.660
It is the most irrational
number.

00:05:01.660 --> 00:05:05.040
The best you can do to
approximate it is to use

00:05:05.040 --> 00:05:07.020
Fibonacci numbers-- two
Fibonacci numbers

00:05:07.020 --> 00:05:08.450
dividing one another.

00:05:08.450 --> 00:05:10.440
Two consecutive Fibonacci
numbers

00:05:10.440 --> 00:05:12.120
divided by one another.

00:05:12.120 --> 00:05:17.730
So 55 divided by 89 would
approximate the golden ratio.

00:05:17.730 --> 00:05:20.720
And we will tell you more about
the golden ratio in our

00:05:20.720 --> 00:05:21.970
upcoming video.

